ve got a pot full of marshmallow. Let the mixture set for a few minutes, remove from the pot, and cut up your marshmallows. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Culinary blog Serious Eats recommends adding a few egg whites when you add gelatin to make the marshmallows even better. If you don't have any gelatin you can also just beat egg whites into the sugar syrup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you make your own marshmallows you can experiment with flavor variations, several of which are detailed at the source link below along with a recipe for vegan marshmallows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.seriouseats.com/2010/12/how-to-make-marshmallows.html"&gt;How to Make Marshmallows&lt;/a&gt; | Serious Eats&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;
